WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.966 --> 00:00:08.884
♪ ♪

2
00:00:08.968 --> 00:00:10.970
[birds chirping]

3
00:00:20.312 --> 00:00:21.647
[crying]

4
00:00:21.731 --> 00:00:23.607
No. don't go!

5
00:00:24.650 --> 00:00:27.069
[Vilya grunts] I'll be back.
Little Flower.

6
00:00:27.153 --> 00:00:31.115
But until then.
you need to know something.

7
00:00:31.198 --> 00:00:32.700
- [sniffling]
- [wind whistling]

8
00:00:32.783 --> 00:00:35.202
Listen to that. Keyleth.

9
00:00:37.329 --> 00:00:40.249
- Do you hear it?
- The wind?

10
00:00:40.332 --> 00:00:42.460
- Your power.
- [gasps]

11
00:00:45.337 --> 00:00:46.839
Whoa.

12
00:00:46.922 --> 00:00:48.924
Now. listen to that.

13
00:00:50.134 --> 00:00:52.887
Wind. fire.

14
00:00:52.970 --> 00:00:55.181
And the earth and water.

15
00:01:01.145 --> 00:01:03.189
- Ow.
- [Vilya] Ah.

16
00:01:03.272 --> 00:01:06.484
Never pull back. Here.

17
00:01:08.068 --> 00:01:10.446
See?

18
00:01:10.529 --> 00:01:12.615
Flame cannot live without air.

19
00:01:12.698 --> 00:01:16.118
and we are Air Ashari.
are we not?

20
00:01:16.202 --> 00:01:19.413
We were made
to pass through fire.

21
00:01:19.497 --> 00:01:21.457
It doesn't hurt you?

22
00:01:21.540 --> 00:01:23.751
Only if you let it.

23
00:01:23.834 --> 00:01:25.377
[Keyleth gasps]

24
00:01:25.461 --> 00:01:26.796
[laughs]

25
00:01:26.879 --> 00:01:30.007
- Time for Mom to go.
- Can I go with you?

26
00:01:30.090 --> 00:01:32.218
You'll always be with me.

27
00:01:32.301 --> 00:01:35.346
And one day. you'll be ready
for your own journey.

28
00:01:35.429 --> 00:01:37.181
You only have to listen.

29
00:01:39.934 --> 00:01:41.769
[receding footsteps]

30
00:01:42.770 --> 00:01:44.772
♪ ♪

31
00:01:55.074 --> 00:01:57.243
♪ ♪

32
00:02:25.980 --> 00:02:28.440
♪ ♪

33
00:02:53.382 --> 00:02:55.175
♪ ♪

34
00:03:01.307 --> 00:03:03.309
[wind whistling softly]

35
00:03:06.395 --> 00:03:08.606
- [wind gusting]
- [gasps]

36
00:03:11.150 --> 00:03:14.194
And then. whoosh.
I was alive again.

37
00:03:14.278 --> 00:03:16.947
It really puts life
into perspective. you know?

38
00:03:17.031 --> 00:03:19.366
I feel more grown. more mature.

39
00:03:19.450 --> 00:03:21.535
Eh. you look more mature.

40
00:03:21.619 --> 00:03:23.704
I'm going to take that
as a compliment

41
00:03:23.787 --> 00:03:25.831
because of how mature I am.

42
00:03:25.915 --> 00:03:27.249
Vax gets it.

43
00:03:27.333 --> 00:03:29.001
- Right. brother?
- Sure.

44
00:03:29.084 --> 00:03:32.379
- Whole new perspective.
- [grunts]

45
00:03:32.463 --> 00:03:34.214
[Pike] Uh. Keyleth?

46
00:03:34.298 --> 00:03:36.675
- Keyleth.
- [gasps]

47
00:03:36.759 --> 00:03:40.512
- Is something wrong?
- No. nothing.

48
00:03:40.596 --> 00:03:44.224
It's just.
we're so close to Pyrah.

49
00:03:44.308 --> 00:03:45.893
[Percy] Is that
where you're from?

50
00:03:45.976 --> 00:03:47.686
No. I'm an Air Ashari.

51
00:03:47.770 --> 00:03:49.897
The Fire Ashari live there.

52
00:03:49.980 --> 00:03:51.774
guarding the rift
to the Fire Plane.

53
00:03:51.857 --> 00:03:53.567
It was one of the last places

54
00:03:53.651 --> 00:03:57.363
my mom was seen alive
on her Aramenté.

55
00:03:57.446 --> 00:04:00.366
Oh. Keyleth. I'm so sorry.

56
00:04:00.449 --> 00:04:03.619
If we're close to Pyrah.
maybe we should go.

57
00:04:03.702 --> 00:04:07.498
I'd like to. but the people of
Tal'Dorei are depending on us.

58
00:04:07.581 --> 00:04:09.416
No. y-you're right.

59
00:04:09.500 --> 00:04:11.585
It's fine. I didn't mean to...

60
00:04:11.669 --> 00:04:13.963
I-I'm gonna go get more wood.

61
00:04:16.840 --> 00:04:19.468
Uh. how long has Grog been gone?

62
00:04:19.551 --> 00:04:21.595
Doesn't take that long
to pop a squat.

63
00:04:21.679 --> 00:04:24.181
This is Grog
we're talking about.

64
00:04:24.264 --> 00:04:27.017
I'll go check on him. Here.

65
00:04:27.101 --> 00:04:28.936
For the fire.

66
00:04:37.403 --> 00:04:40.364
[clears throat] Um. uh...

67
00:04:40.447 --> 00:04:41.699
Craven Edge?

68
00:04:41.782 --> 00:04:44.702
[Craven Edge sighs] Yes?

69
00:04:44.785 --> 00:04:46.745
Ah. good. you're there.

70
00:04:46.829 --> 00:04:49.373
[Craven Edge] I hunger.

71
00:04:49.456 --> 00:04:51.291
Yep. for blood.

72
00:04:51.375 --> 00:04:54.545
Uh. look. so I love opening
people up to feed you. right?

73
00:04:54.628 --> 00:04:57.256
I mean. they're flying apart.
It's like a dream.

74
00:04:57.339 --> 00:04:58.966
Uh. but can I ask.

75
00:04:59.049 --> 00:05:02.469
could you ever be... full?

76
00:05:02.553 --> 00:05:04.304
[Scanlan] Uh. Grog?

77
00:05:04.388 --> 00:05:06.306
- Are you talking to your dookie?
- Uh. yeah.

78
00:05:06.390 --> 00:05:07.933
Just asserting my dominance.

79
00:05:08.017 --> 00:05:10.394
Uh. can you play me a tune?

80
00:05:10.477 --> 00:05:12.229
You know. I just. uh.
I don't want anyone

81
00:05:12.312 --> 00:05:13.647
hearing me go boom-boom.

82
00:05:13.731 --> 00:05:17.026
Sure. yeah. Poop accompaniment.

83
00:05:17.109 --> 00:05:19.361
It's what I've been
training for my whole life.

84
00:05:19.445 --> 00:05:21.447
[clears throat]
<i>♪ In an outhouse ♪</i>

85
00:05:21.530 --> 00:05:22.948
<i>♪ On the edge of the world...</i>

86
00:05:23.032 --> 00:05:25.159
[Grog] Oh. so. um...

87
00:05:25.242 --> 00:05:28.037
- Uh. where was I?
- [Scanlan] Uh. is this loud enough for you?

88
00:05:28.120 --> 00:05:29.747
Uh. yeah. yeah. that's good!

89
00:05:29.830 --> 00:05:33.125
Um. so I kind of
want to know. like. um.

90
00:05:33.208 --> 00:05:35.794
what's in this for you?

91
00:05:35.878 --> 00:05:38.839
[Craven Edge] The blood
of your enemies feeds me.

92
00:05:38.922 --> 00:05:41.592
Their strength becomes yours.

93
00:05:41.675 --> 00:05:43.761
That is our exchange.

94
00:05:43.844 --> 00:05:47.473
Is it? I mean. I am crazy.
no doubt. when I'm using you.

95
00:05:47.556 --> 00:05:50.934
- but it kind of feels...
- It matters not.

96
00:05:51.018 --> 00:05:54.063
- All that matters is...
- [farts]

97
00:05:54.146 --> 00:05:55.939
Ooh. [chuckles] Sorry.

98
00:05:56.023 --> 00:05:59.818
[Craven Edge sighs] I hunger.
always.

99
00:06:01.361 --> 00:06:04.782
Man. I sympathize with that.

100
00:06:06.658 --> 00:06:09.495
[wind howling]

101
00:06:09.578 --> 00:06:11.330
[snoring]

102
00:06:13.332 --> 00:06:14.833
- [wind whooshing]
- [chittering]

103
00:06:24.093 --> 00:06:25.719
[roars]

104
00:06:27.429 --> 00:06:30.224
[people screaming]

105
00:06:30.307 --> 00:06:31.892
[growling]

106
00:06:33.102 --> 00:06:34.770
[grunts]

107
00:06:43.487 --> 00:06:45.322
[whispered voices]

108
00:06:46.740 --> 00:06:48.325
- [screeching]
- No!

109
00:06:48.408 --> 00:06:50.160
Leave me alone!

110
00:06:50.244 --> 00:06:53.163
[panting]

111
00:06:53.247 --> 00:06:55.165
Vax. are-are you okay?

112
00:06:55.249 --> 00:06:58.627
Sorry. I must have dozed off.

113
00:06:58.710 --> 00:07:02.047
- Thought I saw dragons.
- Want me to take over?

114
00:07:02.131 --> 00:07:04.341
No. Rest.

115
00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:06.176
I just need to stretch my legs.

116
00:07:10.973 --> 00:07:12.891
[grunts]

117
00:07:14.560 --> 00:07:15.686
Come on. damn it.

118
00:07:15.769 --> 00:07:18.397
Why won't you come off?

119
00:07:23.777 --> 00:07:25.779
[birds chirping]

120
00:07:29.825 --> 00:07:30.951
[grunts]

121
00:07:31.034 --> 00:07:32.452
[gasps]

122
00:07:33.453 --> 00:07:35.080
[Pike] Sing with me. buddy.

123
00:07:35.164 --> 00:07:37.207
[Pike and Grog] <i>♪ Road. road.
we're on the road ♪</i>

124
00:07:37.291 --> 00:07:39.334
<i>♪ Road. road. we're on
the road ♪</i>

125
00:07:39.418 --> 00:07:43.297
<i>♪ Good thing you and me
ain't choads ♪</i>

126
00:07:43.380 --> 00:07:45.591
<i>♪ We're on the fucking road ♪ ♪</i>

127
00:07:45.674 --> 00:07:47.009
- Ha!
- Aah! Grog!

128
00:07:47.092 --> 00:07:48.510
Oh. sorry.

129
00:07:48.594 --> 00:07:50.637
[Pike] You be careful.
you big old boy.

130
00:07:50.721 --> 00:07:52.431
[Vex] Feel better?

131
00:07:52.514 --> 00:07:55.392
I will when we get there.

132
00:07:55.475 --> 00:07:57.102
[Scanlan grunting]

133
00:07:58.478 --> 00:08:00.480
[panting]

134
00:08:02.691 --> 00:08:04.526
- [Vex] Hey. Scanlan.
- Huh?

135
00:08:04.610 --> 00:08:06.695
You know all these
magical words and such.

136
00:08:06.778 --> 00:08:08.864
Mind taking a peek at this?

137
00:08:08.947 --> 00:08:10.657
What. you kept that thing?

138
00:08:10.741 --> 00:08:12.242
Huh. uh...

139
00:08:12.326 --> 00:08:14.328
[mumbles] "Volantire."

140
00:08:14.411 --> 00:08:17.164
- Oh.
- Holy shit.

141
00:08:17.247 --> 00:08:18.474
What did you...
How did you do that?

142
00:08:18.498 --> 00:08:22.211
What'd you say? Vertuna?
Viridian? Voluptuous?

143
00:08:22.294 --> 00:08:23.712
Mm. venereal.

144
00:08:23.795 --> 00:08:25.380
- [sighs] Dick.
- Whoa.

145
00:08:25.464 --> 00:08:27.382
Okay. okay. okay.
how about this?

146
00:08:27.466 --> 00:08:30.010
I'll tell you the magic word
for a favor.

147
00:08:30.093 --> 00:08:31.345
What favor?

148
00:08:31.428 --> 00:08:33.013
Ooh. yeah. that's the thing.

149
00:08:33.096 --> 00:08:35.432
I'm not gonna tell you.
You just got to trust me.

150
00:08:35.515 --> 00:08:38.894
Ha. I've met cockroaches
more trustworthy than you.

151
00:08:38.977 --> 00:08:40.854
[coughing] Volantire.

152
00:08:40.938 --> 00:08:42.773
- Whoa!
- [Grog] Scanlan. you're a birdie.

153
00:08:42.856 --> 00:08:44.816
[laughs. whoops]

154
00:08:44.900 --> 00:08:46.693
Vex. you are missing out.

155
00:08:46.777 --> 00:08:49.112
You really have
to experience it firsthand

156
00:08:49.196 --> 00:08:52.241
to truly... whoa...
understand the-the...

157
00:08:52.324 --> 00:08:53.825
- What?
- [low rumble]

158
00:08:55.827 --> 00:08:57.371
- Whoa.
- [Vex] Scanlan!

159
00:08:57.454 --> 00:08:59.706
I swear to the gods.
I will restring your lute

160
00:08:59.790 --> 00:09:01.416
with your own pubic hairs!

161
00:09:01.500 --> 00:09:03.669
We don't have time for this.

162
00:09:03.752 --> 00:09:05.087
Uh. guys. there's a volcano.

163
00:09:05.170 --> 00:09:07.047
and it is more pissed off
than Vex.

164
00:09:07.130 --> 00:09:08.382
What?

165
00:09:08.465 --> 00:09:10.467
The volcano is supposed
to be dormant.

166
00:09:10.550 --> 00:09:13.053
Yeah? Well. it's not.

167
00:09:13.136 --> 00:09:15.806
No. The rift
to the Fire Plane is there.

168
00:09:15.889 --> 00:09:18.809
If it's erupting. then Pyrah...

169
00:09:18.892 --> 00:09:21.061
The Fire Ashari
could be in trouble.

170
00:09:21.144 --> 00:09:23.939
Then they'll have to deal
with it themselves.

171
00:09:24.022 --> 00:09:27.901
I'm sorry. Keyleth. but Osysa's
instructions were very clear.

172
00:09:27.985 --> 00:09:29.945
Well. uh... Vex.

173
00:09:32.155 --> 00:09:34.074
[shouts]

174
00:09:36.285 --> 00:09:38.829
- [Vex] Keyleth!
- [screeches]

175
00:09:38.912 --> 00:09:42.541
Man. you could go after her
if you had a flying broom.

176
00:09:42.624 --> 00:09:44.584
All of Tal'Dorei is in danger.

177
00:09:44.668 --> 00:09:47.879
We can't detour every time
we see someone in trouble.

178
00:09:47.963 --> 00:09:50.340
This isn't just someone
in trouble.

179
00:09:50.424 --> 00:09:51.758
It's her people.

180
00:09:51.842 --> 00:09:55.554
Brother. Keyleth would drop
everything to help us.

181
00:09:55.637 --> 00:09:57.681
Especially you.

182
00:09:57.764 --> 00:09:59.683
[grunts softly]

183
00:09:59.766 --> 00:10:01.768
[screeching]

184
00:10:07.149 --> 00:10:09.067
[creatures screeching]

185
00:10:09.151 --> 00:10:11.320
[people shouting]

186
00:10:13.280 --> 00:10:15.157
[shouts]

187
00:10:15.240 --> 00:10:17.326
- Help!
- [screeches]

188
00:10:25.334 --> 00:10:27.169
[gasps softly]

189
00:10:28.253 --> 00:10:29.546
It's okay.

190
00:10:29.629 --> 00:10:31.006
Get to your family.

191
00:10:31.089 --> 00:10:33.091
Thank you.

192
00:10:33.175 --> 00:10:35.052
- Mother!
- [gasps]

193
00:10:35.135 --> 00:10:37.304
[Keyleth] Pyrah.

194
00:10:39.306 --> 00:10:41.433
- [man groans]
- [gasps]

195
00:10:41.516 --> 00:10:42.893
Are you okay?

196
00:10:42.976 --> 00:10:45.395
More are coming through.

197
00:10:45.479 --> 00:10:47.189
- We need help.
- Dad?

198
00:10:47.272 --> 00:10:49.524
Keyleth.

199
00:10:49.608 --> 00:10:51.943
[Keyleth laughs softly]

200
00:10:52.027 --> 00:10:53.528
I didn't know
when I'd see you again.

201
00:10:53.612 --> 00:10:55.280
I can't believe you're here.

202
00:10:55.364 --> 00:10:57.824
You must have come
for your Aramenté.

203
00:10:58.867 --> 00:11:00.577
I-I. uh...

204
00:11:00.660 --> 00:11:03.538
Uh. what did this to Pyrah?
There are so many dead.

205
00:11:03.622 --> 00:11:06.166
The rift to the Fire Plane
was torn open.

206
00:11:06.249 --> 00:11:07.918
That's impossible.

207
00:11:08.001 --> 00:11:09.628
It's been secure
for generations.

208
00:11:09.711 --> 00:11:10.921
It was a dragon.

209
00:11:11.004 --> 00:11:13.090
He laid waste to our people.

210
00:11:13.173 --> 00:11:15.384
[coughing]

211
00:11:15.467 --> 00:11:17.135
[Korrin] You remember Cerkonos?

212
00:11:17.219 --> 00:11:20.180
Of course.
Winds watch you. Headmaster.

213
00:11:20.263 --> 00:11:22.224
And you. Keyleth.

214
00:11:22.307 --> 00:11:24.393
I came as soon as I could.

215
00:11:24.476 --> 00:11:26.812
But our brothers and sisters
were already decimated.

216
00:11:26.895 --> 00:11:28.814
- [crackling rumble]
- [gasping. groaning]

217
00:11:28.897 --> 00:11:32.317
[Cerkonos] If we can't find
a way to close the rift soon.

218
00:11:32.401 --> 00:11:34.861
the Fire Dominion
will consume ours

219
00:11:34.945 --> 00:11:37.072
and remain open forever.

220
00:11:38.240 --> 00:11:41.118
Keyleth. I need you
to come with me.

221
00:11:42.327 --> 00:11:44.913
Normally. the lodestones
keep the gateway sealed.

222
00:11:44.996 --> 00:11:47.040
But when the dragon
destroyed them.

223
00:11:47.124 --> 00:11:48.708
the rift was torn open.

224
00:11:48.792 --> 00:11:51.128
Those beasts have been
coming through in waves

225
00:11:51.211 --> 00:11:53.630
while our firetamers
hold them back.

226
00:11:53.713 --> 00:11:55.757
How do we close the rift?

227
00:11:55.841 --> 00:11:57.968
By controlling
the flames themselves.

228
00:11:58.051 --> 00:11:59.886
The two of us.

229
00:12:01.054 --> 00:12:02.889
Dad. I-I don't know if I...

230
00:12:02.973 --> 00:12:06.017
We're lucky you came.
You've been on your Aramenté.

231
00:12:06.101 --> 00:12:09.813
Your mastery of fire
must be far beyond ours.

232
00:12:09.896 --> 00:12:11.440
Uh. you would think.

233
00:12:11.523 --> 00:12:14.609
The firetamers need
our magic to seal it.

234
00:12:17.529 --> 00:12:19.573
[Kima] More of these fuckers?

235
00:12:19.656 --> 00:12:21.491
- [Korrin] I've brought help!
- Huh?

236
00:12:21.575 --> 00:12:23.869
No freaking way. Keyleth?

237
00:12:23.952 --> 00:12:26.705
Kima? Allura.

238
00:12:28.790 --> 00:12:30.167
But you guys are dead.

239
00:12:30.250 --> 00:12:32.252
We're very much alive.

240
00:12:32.335 --> 00:12:34.129
Where's the rest of your team?

241
00:12:37.257 --> 00:12:40.677
[Kima] Oh. God.
It was a massacre.

242
00:12:40.760 --> 00:12:42.888
- [Vex] Anyone have eyes on Keyleth?
- [screeching]

243
00:12:45.432 --> 00:12:47.225
[Grog] Oh. yeah.

244
00:12:47.309 --> 00:12:49.728
You know what
you fight fire with?

245
00:12:49.811 --> 00:12:51.563
- Fire?
- Me.

246
00:12:51.646 --> 00:12:54.024
[shouts]

247
00:12:54.107 --> 00:12:55.734
[Vex] Trinket.
time to get to work.

248
00:12:55.817 --> 00:12:57.903
[growls]

249
00:12:58.945 --> 00:13:01.490
Scanlan. word. please.

250
00:13:01.573 --> 00:13:03.384
Just say yes to that favor.
and it's all yours.

251
00:13:03.408 --> 00:13:06.203
I hope you fall
into lava. asshat!

252
00:13:06.286 --> 00:13:08.663
Well. that wasn't a no.

253
00:13:08.747 --> 00:13:10.916
<i>- ♪ Let's crank up the heat ♪ ♪</i>
- [gasps]

254
00:13:10.999 --> 00:13:13.251
[shouting]

255
00:13:13.335 --> 00:13:16.046
- Scanlan.
- Keyleth. if we fetch your friends.

256
00:13:16.129 --> 00:13:18.131
can you buy us some time?

257
00:13:18.215 --> 00:13:21.134
I mean. we can
certainly try. [gasps]

258
00:13:21.218 --> 00:13:22.761
Huh?

259
00:13:22.844 --> 00:13:24.471
[Pike] One's coming through!

260
00:13:25.514 --> 00:13:26.723
[Pike and Grog grunting]

261
00:13:26.806 --> 00:13:28.642
- [Pike] It's going.
- [Grog] Hold.

262
00:13:30.352 --> 00:13:33.021
[grunting fiercely]

263
00:13:33.104 --> 00:13:35.649
[Craven Edge] I hunger.

264
00:13:35.732 --> 00:13:37.234
Feed me.

265
00:13:37.317 --> 00:13:41.988
Well. I'm trying. but none of
these guys got bloody insides.

266
00:13:42.072 --> 00:13:43.615
- [Pike] What was that. buddy?
- Uh...

267
00:13:43.698 --> 00:13:46.910
I just love me
some blueberry pie.

268
00:13:46.993 --> 00:13:49.746
- Wh-What?
- Shit. shit. I am very flammable!

269
00:13:54.376 --> 00:13:56.836
[whistles]

270
00:14:04.386 --> 00:14:05.512
- Hey.
- [gasps]

271
00:14:05.595 --> 00:14:07.305
Wait. what?

272
00:14:07.389 --> 00:14:09.849
Allura fucking Vysoren.

273
00:14:09.933 --> 00:14:12.769
Not my middle name. but
I'm pleased to see you as well.

274
00:14:12.852 --> 00:14:15.647
Quickly. Keyleth and her father
need our help.

275
00:14:17.524 --> 00:14:20.151
How are you here?
In Emon. we saw...

276
00:14:20.235 --> 00:14:21.945
Allura saved us.

277
00:14:23.655 --> 00:14:25.240
<i>When the tower fell.</i>

278
00:14:25.323 --> 00:14:28.159
<i>she whisked us away
at the last second.</i>

279
00:14:28.243 --> 00:14:29.452
<i>Nearly shat my armor.</i>

280
00:14:29.536 --> 00:14:31.454
We knew if Thordak was free.

281
00:14:31.538 --> 00:14:33.206
it meant the rift was open.

282
00:14:33.290 --> 00:14:35.500
Hold up. Thordak
came through Pyrah?

283
00:14:35.584 --> 00:14:37.752
How did you even know
it was him?

284
00:14:37.836 --> 00:14:41.047
Because we are the reason
he escaped.

285
00:14:41.131 --> 00:14:44.134
<i>Years ago. Kima and I
battled Thordak</i>

286
00:14:44.217 --> 00:14:46.261
<i>with a group not unlike yours.</i>

287
00:14:48.638 --> 00:14:50.765
[grunting]

288
00:14:50.849 --> 00:14:53.727
<i>- But we were outmatched.</i>
- [growling]

289
00:14:53.810 --> 00:14:55.729
<i>In a desperate attempt.</i>

290
00:14:55.812 --> 00:14:58.189
<i>we got hold
of an ancient artifact.</i>

291
00:14:58.273 --> 00:15:00.483
<i>the Soul Anchor.</i>

292
00:15:00.567 --> 00:15:03.320
<i>and decided to bind him to it.</i>

293
00:15:03.403 --> 00:15:07.240
<i>Like an arcane tether. it pulled
Thordak into the Fire Plane...</i>

294
00:15:09.576 --> 00:15:11.786
<i>...imprisoning him
there forever.</i>

295
00:15:12.829 --> 00:15:14.414
Or so we thought.

296
00:15:14.497 --> 00:15:16.499
[rumbling]

297
00:15:18.418 --> 00:15:21.630
[Korrin] Come. Stay close.

298
00:15:23.673 --> 00:15:25.592
All right. Keyleth. this is it.

299
00:15:25.675 --> 00:15:27.510
No. I-I can't. I can't do it.

300
00:15:27.594 --> 00:15:30.930
Of course you can.
You're as strong as your mother.

301
00:15:31.014 --> 00:15:33.433
Maybe even stronger.

302
00:15:37.729 --> 00:15:39.731
[grunting]

303
00:15:44.069 --> 00:15:45.236
Now!

304
00:15:48.281 --> 00:15:49.783
[grunts]

305
00:15:51.951 --> 00:15:53.787
- [wind whistling]
- [grunts]

306
00:16:01.920 --> 00:16:03.338
Yes.

307
00:16:03.421 --> 00:16:04.798
Good work. Keyleth.

308
00:16:07.467 --> 00:16:08.551
Oh. no.

309
00:16:08.635 --> 00:16:10.303
[shouting. screaming]

310
00:16:15.642 --> 00:16:17.560
[Korrin] Careful.

311
00:16:19.354 --> 00:16:20.271
Look out!

312
00:16:20.355 --> 00:16:22.440
[shouting]

313
00:16:24.150 --> 00:16:26.027
[Korrin] Damn it. it's widening.

314
00:16:26.111 --> 00:16:29.030
[grunting]

315
00:16:30.949 --> 00:16:32.409
[yells]

316
00:16:35.995 --> 00:16:37.664
[Craven Edge] I hunger.

317
00:16:37.747 --> 00:16:40.458
What? They don't got no blood.

318
00:16:40.542 --> 00:16:43.920
[Craven Edge] Then find me
some... now.

319
00:16:44.003 --> 00:16:45.839
- Huh?
- [screeching]

320
00:16:47.507 --> 00:16:49.467
[grunts] I need higher ground.

321
00:16:49.551 --> 00:16:51.720
Okay. fine. It's "Volantire."

322
00:16:51.803 --> 00:16:54.472
Volantire? [shouts. laughs]

323
00:16:57.142 --> 00:16:58.435
That's more like it.

324
00:17:06.317 --> 00:17:07.819
We're losing control.

325
00:17:07.902 --> 00:17:10.029
Everybody. gather round!

326
00:17:12.782 --> 00:17:13.950
Together.

327
00:17:14.033 --> 00:17:15.535
[grunting]

328
00:17:24.169 --> 00:17:25.545
[pained yell]

329
00:17:25.628 --> 00:17:27.130
Dad!

330
00:17:28.131 --> 00:17:29.716
- [groaning]
- Pike!

331
00:17:29.799 --> 00:17:32.177
Oh. no. I got him.

332
00:17:34.345 --> 00:17:36.264
I'm sorry. Dad.

333
00:17:36.347 --> 00:17:39.684
The truth is.
I haven't finished my trials.

334
00:17:39.768 --> 00:17:43.354
I... I'm too scared.
I'm not ready.

335
00:17:43.438 --> 00:17:45.440
[groaning]

336
00:17:47.609 --> 00:17:50.028
[wind whistling]

337
00:17:51.070 --> 00:17:53.907
<i>[Vilya] Little Flower. listen.</i>

338
00:18:00.580 --> 00:18:02.582
<i>Listen.</i>

339
00:18:07.337 --> 00:18:09.923
[Vax] Behind you! Vex!

340
00:18:10.006 --> 00:18:11.633
[indistinct. distant shouting]

341
00:18:11.716 --> 00:18:12.884
[Keyleth whimpers]

342
00:18:12.967 --> 00:18:15.929
<i>[Vilya] Listen to your power.</i>

343
00:18:16.012 --> 00:18:19.390
- [Grog] Damn it!
- [Vax] There's too many of them!

344
00:18:19.474 --> 00:18:22.143
[Keyleth whimpers. shudders]

345
00:18:25.605 --> 00:18:29.400
I am Keyleth. an Air Ashari.

346
00:18:29.484 --> 00:18:32.028
like my mother before me.

347
00:18:32.111 --> 00:18:33.947
[grunting]

348
00:18:37.992 --> 00:18:39.619
Keyleth. what are you doing?

349
00:18:43.665 --> 00:18:44.874
Keyleth?

350
00:18:50.421 --> 00:18:53.341
I was made to pass through fire.

351
00:18:54.342 --> 00:18:55.969
Keyleth!

352
00:19:12.443 --> 00:19:14.195
[Keyleth] The Fire Plane.

353
00:19:17.657 --> 00:19:19.200
Aah! It hurts!

354
00:19:20.827 --> 00:19:22.745
Only if I let it.

355
00:19:26.875 --> 00:19:28.710
[grunts. shouts]

356
00:19:31.129 --> 00:19:33.339
I can hear it.

357
00:19:34.674 --> 00:19:35.967
[gasps]

358
00:19:37.010 --> 00:19:38.928
[screaming]

359
00:19:59.032 --> 00:20:00.950
♪ ♪

360
00:20:03.786 --> 00:20:06.080
[roars]

361
00:20:10.084 --> 00:20:13.087
[bellowing]

362
00:20:15.423 --> 00:20:18.217
[explosive whooshing]

363
00:20:22.221 --> 00:20:24.390
[Vax] Keyleth!

364
00:20:24.474 --> 00:20:26.726
[gasps] No.

365
00:20:31.731 --> 00:20:33.024
[wood clunking]

366
00:20:37.070 --> 00:20:38.780
[wind whistles]

367
00:20:46.788 --> 00:20:48.206
[gasps]

368
00:20:48.289 --> 00:20:50.416
- [grunts]
- My child.

369
00:20:50.500 --> 00:20:52.794
- I thought...
- I'm okay. Dad.

370
00:20:54.087 --> 00:20:55.088
- What?
- [Pike] Keyleth.

371
00:20:55.171 --> 00:20:56.231
[Scanlan] Keyleth.
you're all right.

372
00:20:56.255 --> 00:20:57.382
[Pike] Oh. my God.

373
00:20:57.465 --> 00:20:59.133
[overlapping chatter]

374
00:20:59.217 --> 00:21:00.969
[Scanlan] Holy shit.
that was close.

375
00:21:01.052 --> 00:21:02.887
[Pike] Gave me a heart attack.

376
00:21:04.681 --> 00:21:07.183
Think you'll be needing this.

377
00:21:16.275 --> 00:21:19.153
[Cerkonos] Keyleth
of the Air Ashari.

378
00:21:19.237 --> 00:21:23.658
from this day forward.
you have the blessing of Pyrah.

379
00:21:23.741 --> 00:21:26.995
Your water and earth trials
await you on your Aramenté.

380
00:21:27.078 --> 00:21:31.165
But go forth. knowing
you have mastered fire.

381
00:21:31.249 --> 00:21:33.459
[Keyleth] Thank you.
Flamespeaker.

382
00:21:33.543 --> 00:21:36.879
And a word of warning
on your journeys.

383
00:21:36.963 --> 00:21:38.673
Thordak escaped with aid

384
00:21:38.756 --> 00:21:41.843
from someone posing
as one of our own.

385
00:21:41.926 --> 00:21:44.929
Be sure you trust
those around you.

386
00:21:45.013 --> 00:21:47.974
and truly know their hearts.

387
00:21:48.057 --> 00:21:50.309
I'd trust them with my life.

388
00:21:52.603 --> 00:21:55.106
[laughs softly] Quite the look.

389
00:21:55.189 --> 00:21:57.066
Mind telling us
how you did that?

390
00:21:57.150 --> 00:21:58.609
When the fire took me.

391
00:21:58.693 --> 00:22:01.863
I could feel the connection
between the planes.

392
00:22:01.946 --> 00:22:03.781
Traveling between planes.

393
00:22:03.865 --> 00:22:05.491
Hmm. could be handy.

394
00:22:05.575 --> 00:22:06.909
Think you could do it again?

395
00:22:06.993 --> 00:22:09.370
Only one way to find out.

396
00:22:09.454 --> 00:22:14.083
I couldn't have asked for better
companions for my dear Keyleth.

397
00:22:15.126 --> 00:22:16.753
Until we meet again.

398
00:22:16.836 --> 00:22:18.838
please take care of each other.

399
00:22:18.921 --> 00:22:21.841
Hmm. Especially that one.

400
00:22:24.594 --> 00:22:26.262
Hey. you guys coming with?

401
00:22:26.345 --> 00:22:29.182
Charging into the fray
like the good old days?

402
00:22:29.265 --> 00:22:30.933
[chuckles] Afraid not.

403
00:22:31.017 --> 00:22:33.311
We'll do what we can
to help rebuild Pyrah.

404
00:22:33.394 --> 00:22:37.148
then head to Whitestone
so this one can heal.

405
00:22:39.150 --> 00:22:41.694
Plus. we got to check on
what happened to Syngorn.

406
00:22:41.778 --> 00:22:44.155
Whole city just bugged out
when the dragons showed up.

407
00:22:44.238 --> 00:22:45.364
Elves.

408
00:22:45.448 --> 00:22:47.200
Skittish bunch of bastards.

409
00:22:50.203 --> 00:22:52.121
Oi. Scanlan.

410
00:22:52.205 --> 00:22:54.290
- Mm. Hmm?
- Thanks for earlier.

411
00:22:54.373 --> 00:22:56.209
That was actually kind of you.

412
00:22:56.292 --> 00:22:59.420
I mean. what was I gonna do.
let you die? Again?

413
00:22:59.504 --> 00:23:03.716
And because I'm so mature now.
I accept your terms.

414
00:23:03.800 --> 00:23:06.177
I hereby owe you one favor.

415
00:23:06.260 --> 00:23:09.764
Anything. to be cashed in
at a time of your choosing.

416
00:23:09.847 --> 00:23:13.184
[laughs] Ooh.
This is gonna be fun.

417
00:23:13.267 --> 00:23:15.603
Trinket. care to seal the deal?

418
00:23:15.686 --> 00:23:17.772
[Trinket grumbles]

419
00:23:17.855 --> 00:23:19.357
Hmm? [shouts]

420
00:23:19.440 --> 00:23:21.275
Oh. come on. Oh.

421
00:23:21.359 --> 00:23:24.028
[sighs] Hate that bear.

422
00:23:24.112 --> 00:23:26.364
♪ ♪

423
00:23:26.447 --> 00:23:28.574
[screeches]

424
00:23:31.744 --> 00:23:34.789
- [half-giant] Get back here.
- [screaming]

425
00:23:34.872 --> 00:23:36.833
[grunts. coughs]

426
00:23:36.916 --> 00:23:38.459
- [roaring]
- Huh?

427
00:23:38.543 --> 00:23:41.712
Insects.

428
00:23:49.345 --> 00:23:51.514
Yes.

429
00:23:51.597 --> 00:23:55.101
This gold pleases us.

430
00:23:55.184 --> 00:23:56.686
For now.

431
00:23:56.769 --> 00:23:59.814
And the herd
will keep paying tribute.

432
00:23:59.897 --> 00:24:01.524
For now.

433
00:24:01.607 --> 00:24:03.651
[Umbrasyl] For always.

434
00:24:03.734 --> 00:24:07.196
Nations will quake and tremble

435
00:24:07.280 --> 00:24:10.783
under the reign
of the Chroma Conclave.

436
00:24:10.867 --> 00:24:14.996
[Anna] A reign that will
sadly be short-lived.

437
00:24:15.079 --> 00:24:20.293
Unless. that is. you care
to hear what I have to say.

438
00:24:20.376 --> 00:24:22.378
[Umbrasyl] Hmm...

439
00:24:25.673 --> 00:24:28.217
♪ ♪

440
00:24:28.301 --> 00:24:30.970
<i>♪ In an outhouse
on the edge of the world ♪</i>

441
00:24:31.053 --> 00:24:35.433
<i>♪ Our hearts beat as one ♪</i>

442
00:24:36.851 --> 00:24:39.854
<i>♪ It's where it all ♪</i>

443
00:24:39.937 --> 00:24:44.066
<i>♪ Begun ♪</i>

444
00:24:44.150 --> 00:24:50.156
<i>♪ Standing there
in that privy line ♪</i>

445
00:24:50.239 --> 00:24:54.994
<i>♪ Couldn't help but blush ♪</i>

446
00:24:56.495 --> 00:25:02.043
<i>♪ You sitting in the dark ♪</i>

447
00:25:02.126 --> 00:25:07.298
<i>♪ Me waiting for that flush ♪</i>

448
00:25:07.381 --> 00:25:09.091
<i>♪ Of love ♪ ♪</i>

449
00:25:12.720 --> 00:25:14.680
Chirp.
